title: Extract frames dose not work and receives RuntimeEarning related to numpy and sklearn
body:
First, I would like to thank so much for developing such a great tool. This is definitely a world changing tool. Thank you guys very much. **Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version** Ubuntu 18.04 LTS, with Anaconda env & DeepLabCut2.1.8.2 Please complete the following information about your system: OS: Ubuntu 18.04 DeepLabCut Version: 2.1.8.2 Anaconda env used: yes **Describe the problem** I tried to extract frames for multiple videos at ones. For the first video, received many OMP: KMP_AFFINITY but frames were extracted. However, for the later videos, lots of RunrimeWarning -- overflow / invalid value in numpy and sklearn-- showed up and only one/zero frame was extracted. If I restart the python session and skipped some videos to extract frames, the first video in the ques was done OK but not the later videos. This problem does not occur with other projects with smaller size (640 x 480) videos (Currently trying with FHD) but all the video are playable with VLC player with no problem. When I tried with GUI, same issue comes up. Sometimes the terminal says "Input contains NaN, infinity or a value too large for dtype('float64')". It would be great if I can have some advice to solve this issue. Thank you very much in advance. Please place code inside this:
